  "description": [
    "Friday 19 May 1961 LDO Hopefuls Asked To Delay FR Transfers Navymen who are being con sidered for temporary limited duty officer commissions have been told that they should not also ask to transfer to the Fleet Reserve The Chief of Naval Personnel states BuPers Notice 1830 of 25 April will not approve requests to delay an approved transfer to the Fleet Reserve just so a man can stick around to see if he made the LDO list Commanding officers have also been told not to delay transfers primarily for this purpose Postpone Request The Notice says that an LDO applicant should either postpone requesting Fleet Reserve transfer until after he has heard whether or not he will be commissioned or if he has already put in for Fleet Reserve status he should request withdrawal of the appli cation If the applicant already has a FR transfer date he should request its cancellation When the applicant gets the word as to whether or not he made LDO he can then reapply for authorization to transfer to the Fleet Reserve He will not however rate special considera tion on this application 36 Naval Base Personnel Win E3 Promotion A little something"
  ],
